    54→
    55→---
    56→
    57→## Technical Stack
    58→
    59→### Core Dependencies (to be installed)
    60→
    61→| Package | Version | Purpose | Bundle Impact |
    62→|---------|---------|---------|---------------|
    63→| `@webcontainer/api` | ^1.5.1 | Browser-native Node.js runtime | ~2MB (async loaded) |
    64→| `@xterm/xterm` | ^5.5.0 | Terminal emulator | ~200KB |
    65→| `@xterm/addon-fit` | ^0.10.0 | Auto-resize terminal | ~5KB |
    66→| `@xterm/addon-web-links` | ^0.11.0 | Clickable URLs | ~5KB |
    67→| `@xterm/addon-search` | ^0.15.0 | Find in terminal | ~10KB |
    68→
    69→### Existing Dependencies (already installed)
    70→- `react` ^19.1.0
    71→- `zustand` ^5.0.4
    72→- `react-markdown` (for rendering AI responses)
    73→
    74→### Browser Requirements
    75→- Chrome 89+ / Edge 89+ / Firefox 89+ / Safari 16.4+
    76→- SharedArrayBuffer support (requires COEP/COOP headers)
    77→
    78→---
    79→
    80→## Server Configuration Requirements
    81→
    82→**CRITICAL: No backend/server required. These are HTTP response headers that static hosting provides.**
    83→
    84→### Vite Development Server
    85→
    86→**File:** `vite.config.ts`
    87→**Current State:** Lines 1-111 (server config starts ~line 15)
    88→
    89→**Exact Change Required:**
    90→
    91→```typescript
    92→// In vite.config.ts, add to the server object:
    93→server: {
    94→  port: 3000,
    95→  host: true,
    96→  // ADD THESE TWO LINES:
    97→  headers: {
    98→    'Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy': 'require-corp',
    99→    'Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy': 'same-origin',
   100→  },
   101→},
   102→```
   103→
   104→### Production Deployment (Cloudflare Pages)
   105→
   106→**File:** Create new file `public/_headers`
   107→
   108→```
   109→/*
   110→  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
   111→  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
   112→```
   113→
   114→Cloudflare Pages automatically reads `public/_headers` and applies these headers to all responses.
   115→
   116→### Why These Headers?
   117→
   118→WebContainers uses `SharedArrayBuffer` for high-performance memory operations between WASM and JavaScript. Browsers require Cross-Origin Isolation to enable `SharedArrayBuffer` as a security measure against Spectre-style side-channel attacks.
   119→
   120→**Impact Assessment:**
   121→- May affect third-party iframes (YouTube embeds, etc.)
   122→- Mitigation: Use `crossorigin` attribute on external resources
   123→- Test existing features after enabling headers
   124→
   125→---
   126→
   127→## Phase 1: Terminal UI Foundation
   128→
   129→### Goal
   130→Replace current chat-bubble UI in AITerminal with real xterm.js terminal emulator
   131→
   132→### Dependencies to Install
   133→
   134→```bash
   135→npm install @xterm/xterm@^5.5.0 @xterm/addon-fit@^0.10.0 @xterm/addon-web-links@^0.11.0 @xterm/addon-search@^0.15.0
   136→```
   137→
   138→### Files to Create
   139→
   140→#### 1.1 Directory Structure
   141→
   142→```
   143→src/
   144→├── components/
   145→│   └── PhantomShell/
   146→│       ├── index.ts              # Barrel export
